text:
An apache httpd module implemented with C++ cannot be loaded if call a 
function from unixd.h (built with g++/libtool).  Why not add extern "C" 
linkage specification inside this header?  This looks not consistent with 
other header include style,

  extern "C" {
  #include "unixd.h"
  }
  // ...
  unixd_set_global_mutex_perms(...);
  // ...
